Pxlkit Commercial Terms
=======================

These terms apply only to assets covered by `LICENSE-ASSETS`.
MIT-licensed code packages such as `@pxlkit/core`, `@pxlkit/ui-kit`, and `@pxlkit/voxel`
do not require a paid license or attribution.

License tiers
-------------

1. Community (free)
- Scope: icon packs and other Pxlkit assets
- Projects: unlimited
- Commercial use: yes
- Attribution: required
- Includes: all current asset packs available in this repository

2. Indie ($9.50 one-time)
- Scope: icon packs and other Pxlkit assets
- Projects: 1 shipped product
- Commercial use: yes
- Attribution: not required
- Includes: lifetime rights for that product and updates available at time of purchase

3. Team ($24.50 one-time)
- Scope: icon packs and other Pxlkit assets
- Projects: unlimited
- Commercial use: yes
- Attribution: not required
- Includes: lifetime rights, all current and future asset packs, and priority support

Clarifications
--------------
- SaaS, client work, internal tools, closed-source apps, and marketing sites are allowed under all tiers.
- The paid tiers remove attribution for assets; they do not change the trademark policy.
- End users of your shipped product do not need their own license.
- A `project` means one product, app, or site identified by a single product name, domain, or app-store listing.
- Existing paying customers keep their previously purchased rights. This licensing cleanup is intended to clarify scope, not reduce rights that were already granted for valid Indie or Team purchases.

For purchases or custom terms: https://pxlkit.xyz/pricing or info@pxlkit.xyz
